story.title: Rabid - Episode 2
story.storyDescription: When squirrels suddenly start attacking people, Stephanie’s entire existence is in danger...
story.creator: web-uploader
story.prePaywallNotification: The evil squirrels have returned! Continue RABID to see what happens next.
story.postPaywallNotification: Will Archer’s mother let him go?! Finish RABID to find out.

messages.text: Multiple reports of squirrel attacks in Brooklyn and Queens. Except for emergencies, remain inside.
No. I ran away before the squirrel could get me.
But then I tripped down some stairs and broke my arm.
Are you sure it was going to attack you?
You saw the alert! They’re attacking people again!
In Brooklyn and Queens. Not here in Manhattan.
I’m sorry I can’t come out to be with you.
They’re telling everyone to stay inside just in case.
I’m flying home to Milwaukee tonight.
There was one seat left on the plane.
Apparently other people want to get out of here too.
I’m going to stay with my parents while my arm heals.
My boss said it would be okay.
But I didn’t even get a chance to see you!
I know, but all this stuff with the squirrels has really taken a lot out of me.
I just want to go home and be taken care of.
There’s nothing like a mother’s love.
You of all people should understand that.
Do I detect some sarcasm there?
Maybe a little. You know how I feel about you living at home.
I’m getting close. I looked at a few apartments the other day.
No. They weren’t quite right. The agent knows of some others though.
I will—And please come back soon!
I will, as soon as my arm improves. Bye, Archer.
It will be another month before it fully heals.
I am dying to see you…
I’m thinking of moving back here.
My company is willing let me work remotely.
Plus, the squirrels here in Milwaukee behave normally.
But you know they figured out what happened with those squirrels.
They said it was the frequency coming from that one Long Island power plant.
It caused all the squirrels to go crazy.
Although my mom said it was something different…
She said someone in Brooklyn was setting them off.
What a weird thing for your mom to say.
I know, but the important thing is, there haven’t been any attacks in two weeks.
You keep saying you’re going to move out of your mother’s apartment…
This time it’s going to happen.
Yeah. I wanted to wait to tell you in person but…
It’s a beautiful two-bedroom in Chelsea!
And I think we should move in…together.
Maybe. I’ll think about coming back to New York…
But I’m not ready to move in with you.
Will you at least give our relationship a chance?
Idk. What does your mother think about you moving?
She won’t be happy about it.
But there’s nothing she can do.
I have to come back to New York anyway, even if I decide to move out.
I’ll need to pack my stuff.
Are you back on New York soil yet?
Can you meet me at my place?
My mom just fell on the sidewalk outside.
But I’m taking her to the hospital just in case.
Multiple squirrel attacks reported again in Brooklyn and Queens. Stay inside except for emergencies.
Nice of you to check in—twelve hours later.
Don’t you remember? My mom fell…
She’s fine. But she was scared.
Aren’t you going to ask how I am?
I threw my luggage at the squirrel and managed to get inside my apartment building before it attacked me.
I don’t even want to hear it.
Turns out there were issues with it.
I decided not to sign the lease.
Of course. I figured it would fall through.
I know. Nothing compares to a mother’s love.
Stephanie left New York and never returned—
She moved on to bigger and better things.
Archer never moved out of his mother’s apartment.
Although experts said it was an electrical problem that set the squirrels off,
The squirrels of New York never got angry again.
